<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870330-0154 </DOCNO><HL> Advanced Tobacco to JoinPharmacia Unit in Venture</HL><DD> 03/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ATPI </IN><DATELINE> SAN ANTONIO, Texas  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Advanced Tobacco Products Inc. said it agreed with Leo AB of Helsingborg, Sweden, to develop jointly a smoking deterrent product using Advanced Tobacco nicotine technology.    Under terms of the letter of intent, Leo, a unit of Pharmacia AB, also has the option to acquire exclusive world-wide licensing rights for the new product in exchange for additional cash payments and royalties.    Advanced Tobacco, a maker of a smokeless cigarettes, said Leo will obtain exclusive rights to evaluate Advanced Tobacco's nicotine technology through this July in exchange for certain payments, including non-refundable royalties. Advanced Tobacco declined to disclose further details until a definitive agreement has been reached. </TEXT></DOC>